# AI Virtual Try-On Application -- Complete Product and Implementation Plan

## 1. Product Overview

An AI-powered virtual try-on (AI换衣) web application that lets users upload a photo of a person and a clothing item, then uses an AI model to generate a realistic image of the person wearing that clothing. The app follows a simple three-step flow: **Upload Person** -> **Select Clothing** -> **View Result**.

---

## 2. Design System

### 2.1 Color Palette (Teal/Cyan Dark Theme)

The theme is built on a deep slate/charcoal background with teal/cyan as the primary accent. All colors are specified as HSL CSS custom variables, matching the shadcn/ui variable system already configured in `/app/tailwind.config.ts`.

The following values should be placed inside the `:root` and `.dark` layers in `/app/src/index.css`. Since this is a dark-themed app, the `:root` selector itself will carry the dark values (no separate light mode needed for v1).

```css
@layer base {
  :root {
    /* Base backgrounds - deep charcoal/slate */
    --background: 220 20% 6%;          /* #0d1017 - near-black with blue tint */
    --foreground: 210 20% 92%;         /* #e6eaf0 - soft white */

    /* Cards - slightly elevated surfaces */
    --card: 220 18% 10%;               /* #161b24 */
    --card-foreground: 210 20% 92%;

    /* Popovers/dropdowns */
    --popover: 220 18% 10%;
    --popover-foreground: 210 20% 92%;

    /* Primary - teal/cyan accent */
    --primary: 174 72% 46%;            /* #21b8a8 - rich teal */
    --primary-foreground: 220 20% 6%;  /* dark text on teal */

    /* Secondary - muted slate */
    --secondary: 220 16% 16%;          /* #232832 */
    --secondary-foreground: 210 15% 78%;

    /* Muted - subtle backgrounds */
    --muted: 220 16% 14%;              /* #1e2330 */
    --muted-foreground: 215 15% 55%;   /* #7a8599 */

    /* Accent - warm amber/gold for secondary emphasis */
    --accent: 36 90% 55%;              /* #e8a020 - warm gold */
    --accent-foreground: 220 20% 6%;

    /* Destructive - error red */
    --destructive: 0 72% 51%;          /* #de3a3a */
    --destructive-foreground: 210 20% 92%;

    /* Borders and inputs */
    --border: 220 16% 18%;             /* #272d3a */
    --input: 220 16% 18%;
    --ring: 174 72% 46%;               /* teal ring to match primary */

    /* Border radius */
    --radius: 0.75rem;

    /* Sidebar (not used in v1 but provided for shadcn compat) */
    --sidebar-background: 220 18% 8%;
    --sidebar-foreground: 210 20% 92%;
    --sidebar-primary: 174 72% 46%;
    --sidebar-primary-foreground: 220 20% 6%;
    --sidebar-accent: 220 16% 16%;
    --sidebar-accent-foreground: 210 15% 78%;
    --sidebar-border: 220 16% 18%;
    --sidebar-ring: 174 72% 46%;
  }
}
```

### 2.2 Custom Utility Colors and Gradients (added to tailwind.config.ts)

Extend the `colors` section in `/app/tailwind.config.ts` with:

```ts
// Add to theme.extend.colors:
teal: {
  400: 'hsl(174, 72%, 56%)',
  500: 'hsl(174, 72%, 46%)',
  600: 'hsl(174, 72%, 36%)',
},
gold: {
  400: 'hsl(36, 90%, 65%)',
  500: 'hsl(36, 90%, 55%)',
},
```

And add these keyframes and animations:

```ts
// Add to theme.extend.keyframes:
'shimmer': {
  '0%': { backgroundPosition: '-200% 0' },
  '100%': { backgroundPosition: '200% 0' },
},
'pulse-glow': {
  '0%, 100%': { boxShadow: '0 0 20px hsl(174, 72%, 46%, 0.15)' },
  '50%': { boxShadow: '0 0 40px hsl(174, 72%, 46%, 0.35)' },
},
'float': {
  '0%, 100%': { transform: 'translateY(0px)' },
  '50%': { transform: 'translateY(-6px)' },
},
'slide-reveal': {
  '0%': { clipPath: 'inset(0 100% 0 0)' },
  '100%': { clipPath: 'inset(0 0 0 0)' },
},

// Add to theme.extend.animation:
'shimmer': 'shimmer 2s linear infinite',
'pulse-glow': 'pulse-glow 3s ease-in-out infinite',
'float': 'float 3s ease-in-out infinite',
'slide-reveal': 'slide-reveal 0.8s ease-out forwards',
```

### 2.3 Custom CSS Utilities (in index.css)

```css
@layer utilities {
  .gradient-primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(174, 72%, 46%), hsl(190, 80%, 50%));
  }
  .gradient-warm {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(36, 90%, 55%), hsl(20, 85%, 55%));
  }
  .gradient-surface {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, hsl(220, 18%, 12%), hsl(220, 18%, 8%));
  }
  .glass {
    background: hsl(220, 18%, 10%, 0.7);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border: 1px solid hsl(220, 16%, 20%, 0.5);
  }
  .glow-teal {
    box-shadow: 0 0 30px hsl(174, 72%, 46%, 0.2), 0 0 60px hsl(174, 72%, 46%, 0.1);
  }
  .text-gradient-primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, hsl(174, 72%, 56%), hsl(190, 80%, 60%));
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }
}
```

### 2.4 Global Style Resets (in index.css, replace App.css content)

The existing `/app/src/App.css` contains `#root` constraints that should be removed. The `index.css` global base styles should include:

```css
@layer base {
  * {
    @apply border-border;
  }
  body {
    @apply bg-background text-foreground antialiased;
    font-feature-settings: "rlig" 1, "calt" 1;
  }
  #root {
    @apply min-h-screen;
  }
}
```

---

## 3. Page Structure and Routing

The app is a single-page tool with an optional result/history view. Routing changes in `/app/src/App.tsx`:

| Route | Page Component | Purpose |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| `/` | `TryOnPage` | Main try-on tool with 3-step flow |
| `/result/:id` | `ResultPage` | Full-screen result view with download and before/after comparison |
| `*` | `NotFound` | 404 page (already exists) |

The main page (`TryOnPage`) will use an internal step-based flow managed by Zustand, not separate routes. The three steps are:
1. **Upload** -- Upload person photo and clothing image
2. **Processing** -- AI generation in progress with animated progress
3. **Result** -- Before/after comparison with download

---

## 4. Component Architecture

### 4.1 Layout Components

**`/app/src/components/layout/Header.tsx`**
- App logo/wordmark ("TryOn AI" or similar brand name)
- Minimal navigation: just the app name on the left, a "New Try-On" button on the right
- Glass morphism background with blur
- Uses Framer Motion for mount animation
- Height: h-16, fixed at top with z-50

**`/app/src/components/layout/Footer.tsx`**
- Minimal footer with attribution text
- "Powered by AI" badge
- Links to privacy/terms if needed later

**`/app/src/components/layout/PageContainer.tsx`**
- Wrapper providing consistent padding, max-width (max-w-6xl), and centered layout
- Handles the gradient background pattern (subtle radial gradient dot pattern or mesh gradient)

### 4.2 Upload Components

**`/app/src/components/upload/ImageDropZone.tsx`**
- Reusable drag-and-drop image upload zone
- Props: `label: string`, `description: string`, `icon: LucideIcon`, `onImageSelect: (file: File) => void`, `preview: string | null`, `aspectHint?: string`
- Features:
  - Dashed border container with hover/drag-over state animations
  - Drag-over state: border goes teal, background tints, pulse-glow animation
  - Click to open file picker (hidden `<input type="file" accept="image/*">`)
  - Shows preview thumbnail after selection with a "Remove" overlay button
  - File size validation (max 10MB) with toast error
  - Image type validation (jpg, png, webp)
  - Framer Motion: `whileHover` scale, `animate` for drag states
- Dimensions: w-full, aspect-[3/4] for person, aspect-square for clothing

**`/app/src/components/upload/PersonUpload.tsx`**
- Wraps `ImageDropZone` with person-specific props
- Icon: `User` from lucide-react
- Label: "Upload Your Photo"
- Description: "Drag & drop or click to upload a full-body photo"
- Tip text below: "Best results with clear, well-lit, front-facing photos"

**`/app/src/components/upload/ClothingUpload.tsx`**
- Wraps `ImageDropZone` with clothing-specific props
- Icon: `Shirt` from lucide-react
- Label: "Choose Clothing"
