## 9. Key Component Implementation Details

### 9.1 ImageDropZone Behavior

```
States:
  idle      -> dashed border (border-border), icon + text centered
  hover     -> border-primary/50, slight bg tint, scale(1.02)
  dragOver  -> border-primary, bg-primary/5, pulse-glow animation, "Drop here" text
  hasImage  -> shows preview image filling container, "Change" overlay on hover
  error     -> border-destructive, error text shown briefly
```

Event handling:
- `onDragEnter/onDragOver`: prevent default, set dragOver state
- `onDragLeave`: reset state (with event target check to handle child events)
- `onDrop`: validate file, call `onImageSelect`
- `onClick`: trigger hidden file input

### 9.2 BeforeAfterSlider Implementation

The slider is implemented without external libraries:

```
Container (relative, overflow-hidden, rounded-lg)
  ├── After image (absolute, full size) -- the AI result
  ├── Before image (absolute, full size, clip-path based on slider position)
  ├── Divider line (absolute, left = sliderPosition%)
  │   └── Grab handle (circle, centered on divider)
  ├── "Before" label (absolute, top-left)
  └── "After" label (absolute, top-right)
```

- State: `sliderPosition` (0-100, default 50)
- Mouse events: `onMouseDown` on handle starts tracking, `onMouseMove` on container updates position, `onMouseUp` stops
- Touch events: same flow with `onTouchStart/Move/End`
- Clip-path on before image: `inset(0 ${100 - sliderPosition}% 0 0)`

### 9.3 ProcessingView Status Flow

The processing view simulates progress while polling:

```
0-15%   (0-3s):     "Analyzing your photo..."
15-40%  (3-8s):     "Understanding the garment..."
40-70%  (8-15s):    "Fitting the clothing..."
70-90%  (15-25s):   "Adding finishing touches..."
90-100% (on done):  "Complete!"
```

A `useEffect` with `setInterval` increments progress gradually. When the poll returns `succeeded`, progress jumps to 100% and after 500ms transitions to the result step.

